00:33:17,220 --> 00:33:18,180
preparing to buy it.

586
00:33:19,420 --> 00:33:20,740
With the family in this situation,

587
00:33:20,740 --> 00:33:22,020
why buy a tea hill?

588
00:33:22,300 --> 00:33:23,180
What do you know?

589
00:33:23,180 --> 00:33:24,420
That's called having a vision.

590
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:26,860
What's the use of that?

591
00:33:29,220 --> 00:33:30,380
It's been a year now.

592
00:33:31,020 --> 00:33:32,180
Do you think Sixi has accepted

593
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:33,800
that Jing Kan is gone?

594
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:36,700
Who could accept that?

595
00:33:37,180 --> 00:33:38,020
Could you?

596
00:33:38,460 --> 00:33:39,520
I'd go crazy if it were me.

597
00:33:40,620 --> 00:33:42,900
But she hasn't cried

598
00:33:43,060 --> 00:33:43,980
or even mentioned it.

599
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:45,180
No one knows what's going on.

600
00:33:46,860 --> 00:33:48,340
You'd cry privately, right?

601
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:50,420
Besides, crying isn't going

602
00:33:50,420 --> 00:33:51,820
to bring the dead back to life.

603
00:33:51,820 --> 00:33:53,100
You just expect people to cry.

604
00:33:53,100 --> 00:33:54,220
What are you talking about?

605
00:33:54,320 --> 00:33:55,180
Sixi's here.

606
00:33:55,180 --> 00:33:56,660
We were talking about your tea hill.

607
00:33:56,660 --> 00:33:57,620
It's been settled.

608
00:33:57,740 --> 00:33:58,620
That's great.

609
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:00,180
- Hurry up and eat.
- Okay.

610
00:34:00,180 --> 00:34:01,700
- Eat.
- You came back just in time.

611
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:04,260
Auntie is good.

612
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,820
She even made meat dishes today.

613
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:06,700
It must've cost a lot.

614
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:08,180
She knows you work hard.

615
00:34:08,420 --> 00:34:09,560
- Eat more meat.
- Okay.

616
00:34:12,700 --> 00:34:13,660
I have another thing.

617
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:17,040
I've found a good location
for the branch store.

618
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,240
It will open in a few days.

619
00:34:18,740 --> 00:34:19,660
That's good.

620
00:34:19,900 --> 00:34:21,460
- We'll be busy.
- It's a good thing.

621
00:34:21,700 --> 00:34:22,620
So, Zhenzhu,

622
00:34:22,980 --> 00:34:24,100
it's not quite right for you

623
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:25,020
to keep helping here.

624
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:26,400
I want to ask you

625
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:28,280
to become the Chief
of the Anping Bridge Shop.

626
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:32,220
No, no, no.

627
00:34:32,220 --> 00:34:33,820
You can't joke about this.

628
00:34:34,820 --> 00:34:35,740
Here's the thing.

629
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:36,740
Sixi,

630
00:34:36,740 --> 00:34:39,260
though I used to want your shop,

631
00:34:39,820 --> 00:34:41,740
Donglin already has

632
00:34:41,740 --> 00:34:43,060
seven or eight shops now.

633
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:44,500
I don't even want to go there.

634
00:34:44,980 --> 00:34:46,340
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

635
00:34:46,340 --> 00:34:48,380
I don't even want to be
in charge of the Tea Guild.

636
00:34:48,380 --> 00:34:49,540
Aren't you going to regret it?

637
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:50,540
What's there to regret?

638
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:51,780
It's not easy to get pregnant.

639
00:34:51,780 --> 00:34:52,460
Shouldn't I rest?

640
00:34:53,420 --> 00:34:55,060
I'm just afraid

641
00:34:55,180 --> 00:34:56,460
you'll want it later.

642
00:34:56,460 --> 00:34:57,900
My goodness, don't be afraid.

643
00:34:57,900 --> 00:34:58,860
I won't want it.

644
00:35:02,260 --> 00:35:04,100
Sixi, how about letting me be

645
00:35:04,740 --> 00:35:05,940
the Chief of the branch store?

646
00:35:06,740 --> 00:35:07,660
You?

647
00:35:09,140 --> 00:35:10,860
I'm a little afraid now.

648
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:11,820
Really afraid.

649
00:35:12,540 --> 00:35:13,540
Sit down and eat.

650
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:15,340
I've had someone in mind

651
00:35:15,340 --> 00:35:16,700
for the Chief of the branch store.

652
00:35:19,060 --> 00:35:20,020
Hurry up and eat.

653
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:32,380
Mother,

654
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:34,620
I heard

655
00:35:35,140 --> 00:35:36,700
the other day

656
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:39,940
that people are saying

657
00:35:40,740 --> 00:35:41,700
the Jing Clan still has

658
00:35:42,860 --> 00:35:44,100
a daughter-in-law like me

659
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:45,780
at home.

660
00:35:46,620 --> 00:35:48,220
You're my daughter-in-law,

661
00:35:49,420 --> 00:35:51,660
and even I won't pursue this.

662
00:35:51,980 --> 00:35:53,740
What does it have to do
with anyone else?

663
00:35:56,260 --> 00:35:57,180
Besides,

664
00:35:58,060 --> 00:35:59,660
who hasn't done foolish things

665
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:02,260
when they were young?

666
00:36:04,300 --> 00:36:05,260
Zhusi,

667
00:36:05,780 --> 00:36:07,380
it's only when I reached my age

668
00:36:07,740 --> 00:36:08,740
that I realized

669
00:36:09,580 --> 00:36:10,540
the things

670
00:36:10,780 --> 00:36:12,660
that used to seem important to you

671
00:36:13,180 --> 00:36:14,420
actually aren't that important.

672
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:15,900
It's the things

673
00:36:15,900 --> 00:36:17,180
that seem unimportant

674
00:36:17,940 --> 00:36:19,380
that are truly important.

675
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:24,060
So, what's unimportant?

676
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:26,940
Anything that bothers you
is unimportant.

677
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:29,100
So, what's important then?

678
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:31,900
Playing madiao.

679
00:36:32,580 --> 00:36:35,940
Yes, playing madiao
is the most important.

680
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:37,300
Let's play madiao.

681
00:36:38,580 --> 00:36:40,300
You hung up that sheet?

682
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:41,220
You're here.

683
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:42,700
- What's wrong?
- Zhusi.

684
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:44,780
My waist feels like it's broken.

685
00:36:47,820 --> 00:36:49,860
- Alright, Mother.
- My hands hurt.

686
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:51,380
After thinking it over,

687
00:36:51,380 --> 00:36:53,260
I think we need to find a maid.

688
00:36:54,140 --> 00:36:56,100
I haven't washed clothes for years.

689
00:36:56,220 --> 00:36:57,140
It's not feasible

690
00:36:57,140 --> 00:36:58,420
to rely just on me and Cuiying.

691
00:36:59,780 --> 00:37:01,820
Muyun, you finally changed your mind.

692
00:37:03,460 --> 00:37:05,300
If you're going to find maids,

693
00:37:05,620 --> 00:37:06,580
find three.

694
00:37:07,140 --> 00:37:08,140
One to wash,

695
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:09,420
one to wring,

696
00:37:09,580 --> 00:37:10,660
and one to hang.

697
00:37:10,860 --> 00:37:11,780
Perfect.

698
00:37:12,100 --> 00:37:13,380
As if I don't know

699
00:37:13,380 --> 00:37:14,300
what you're thinking.

700
00:37:14,540 --> 00:37:15,420
Forget about three.

701
00:37:15,420 --> 00:37:17,220
I don't even want to find one.

702
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:20,100
By the way,

703
00:37:20,100 --> 00:37:20,980
Zhusi,

704
00:37:20,980 --> 00:37:22,160
about Aji's betrothal gifts,

705
00:37:22,340 --> 00:37:23,300
what should we say?

706
00:37:26,420 --> 00:37:27,300
His parents

707
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:28,700
